        <abstract> 
<p>Returns CD’s MS [of entomological section of <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi>] marked with suggested alterations.</p>  
<p>Suggests qualifications about rudimentary horn in female <hi rend="italic">Onitis furcifer</hi> [See <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 1: 372].</p>  
<p>Sends additional data on colour differences in sexes of longicorn Coleoptera [See <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 1: 367–8].</p> 
            <p>Suggests a modification of CD’s view of female coloration that would bring him "nearly into harmony" with Wallace.</p>
        </abstract>
